

## Method 1: Using Nginx (With a Bind Mount)

This method links a folder on your local computer directly to the container. Any changes you make to the HTML file will update instantly in the browser.

### 1. Create your project folder and enter it

Open Git Bash and run:

```bash
mkdir -p ~/nginx-site && cd ~/nginx-site

```

### 2. Create the HTML file

Replace `Your Name` and `Your PRN Number` with your actual details:

```bash
echo "<h1>Name: Your Name</h1><h2>PRN: Your PRN Number</h2>" > index.html

```

### 3. Run the Nginx container

Run the container, mapping port `9100` on your computer to port `80` inside the container:

```bash
docker run -d --name my-nginx-container -p 9100:80 -v /$(pwd):/usr/share/nginx/html nginx

```

*(Note: The extra forward slash before `$(pwd)` ensures Git Bash handles the Windows path format correctly).*

### 4. Test it

Open your browser and go to: **`http://localhost:9100`**

