## Method 2: Using Apache / httpd (With a Dockerfile)

This method builds a brand-new, standalone Docker image that contains your webpage baked right inside it.

### 1. Create a new folder and enter it

Open Git Bash and run:

```bash
mkdir -p ~/apache-site && cd ~/apache-site

```

### 2. Create the HTML file

Replace `Your Name` and `Your PRN Number` with your actual details:

```bash
echo "<h1>Name: Your Name</h1><h2>PRN: Your PRN Number</h2>" > index.html

```

### 3. Create the Dockerfile

Run this command to automatically generate the `Dockerfile`:

```bash
cat <<EOF > Dockerfile
FROM httpd:latest
COPY index.html /usr/local/apache2/htdocs/index.html
EOF

```

### 4. Build the custom Docker image

Build an image named `my-apache-image`:

```bash
docker build -t my-apache-image .

```

### 5. Run the container

Run a container using your newly built image on port `9100`:

```bash
docker run -d --name my-apache-container -p 9100:80 my-apache-image

```

